text: Shovel Creek is a stream in the U.S. states of Oregon and Washington. It is a tributary of the Snake River. Shovel Creek was named for the fact prospectors had dug for gold along the stream. ==See also== *List of rivers of Washington ==References== Category:Rivers of Asotin County, Washington Category:Rivers of Wallowa County, Oregon Category:Rivers of Oregon Category:Rivers of Washington (state)
title: Shovel Creek (Snake River tributary)
